<%# app/views/pages/retreat.html.erb %>
<% content_for :title, "The Retreat — The Anchorpoint Retreat" %>
<% content_for :description, "Explore our private mountain chalet in Alma, Colorado — created for focused work, quiet resets, small leadership retreats, and year-round mountain adventure." %>

<section class="section banner-home" style="background-image: url('<%= asset_path('home/backg1-1920-900.jpg') %>'); background-position: center center !important; min-height: 50vh;">
    <div class="hero-container">
        <div class="banner-home-container text-center">
            <h1 class="banner-home-title">The Anchorpoint Retreat</h1>
            <p class="banner-home-excerpt">A Private Mountain Chalet in Alma, Colorado</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="hero-container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8">
                <span class="sub-heading">The Property</span>
                <h2>Modern Alpine Retreat Near Breckenridge</h2>
                <p>A private mountain chalet in Alma, Colorado, created for focused work, quiet resets, small leadership retreats, and year-round mountain adventure.</p>
                <p class="text-muted"><i class="fa-solid fa-location-dot accent-color"></i> 2586 County Road 12, Alma, CO 80420</p>
                <p>Set near the base of Mosquito Pass, this contemporary 2022 chalet gives guests the space to step away from daily noise and reconnect with clear thinking, nature, and meaningful conversation. It is best suited for founder retreats, executive resets, strategy weekends, remote-work stays, couples retreats, and small-group mountain escapes.</p>

                <h3 class="mt-4">Property Highlights</h3>
                <ul class="property-highlights">
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> Contemporary mountain chalet built in 2022</li>
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> 1 bedroom, 1 bathroom, plus a spacious loft for additional sleeping, work, reading, or creative space</li>
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> 1,080 sq ft with soaring 16-foot ceilings and natural light</li>
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> Beetle kill pine accents, butcher block counters, stainless steel appliances, and electric fireplace</li>
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> Quiet alpine valley setting near the base of Mosquito Pass</li>
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> Mountain, meadow, and forest views with frequent wildlife sightings</li>
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> Well, underground power, and septic holding tank</li>
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> About 5 minutes from Alma and about 30 minutes from Breckenridge</li>
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> Ideal for focused retreats, remote work, ski weekends, fishing trips, hiking, and quiet mountain resets</li>
                    <li><i class="fa-solid fa-check accent-color"></i> Best suited for short-stay and part-time use consistent with county guidelines</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="mt-4">Check-in / Check-out</h3>
                <p>Check-in: 3:00 PM &nbsp;|&nbsp; Check-out: 11:00 AM</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="card p-4">
                    <h3 class="heading-sm">Quick Specs</h3>
                    <table class="specs-table">
                        <tr><td>Bedrooms</td><td>1 bed</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Bathrooms</td><td>1 bath</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Max Guests</td><td>4 (ideal for 1–2 couples or small groups)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Square Feet</td><td>1,080 sq ft</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Year Built</td><td>2022</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Location</td><td>Alma, CO 80420</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Check-in</td><td>3:00 PM</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Check-out</td><td>11:00 AM</td></tr>
                    </table>
                    <p class="mt-3 mb-0 small text-muted">Best suited for short-stay and part-time use consistent with county guidelines</p>
                    <a href="/availability" class="btn btn-accent w-100 mt-3">Check Availability</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="gallery" class="section-px-pt-small">
    <div class="hero-container text-center mb-4">
        <span class="sub-heading">Gallery</span>
        <h2>Photo Tour</h2>
    </div>
