<section id="nearby-activities" class="section-px-pt-small">
    <div class="hero-container text-center mb-4">
        <span class="sub-heading">Explore the Area</span>
        <h2>Nearby Activities</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-container">
        <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-2 g-4">
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100 p-4">
                    <h3 class="heading-sm"><i class="fa-solid fa-snowflake accent-color"></i> Breckenridge Skiing and Winter Activities</h3>
                    <p>Breckenridge is about 30 minutes away and offers skiing, snowboarding, snowshoeing, dog sledding, sleigh rides, ice skating, dining, shopping, and seasonal events. Guests get access to a major Colorado resort town while staying in a quieter alpine setting away from the main tourist corridor.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.breckenridge.com/explore-the-resort/activities-and-events/winter-activities.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline-accent btn-sm">Learn More <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100 p-4">
                    <h3 class="heading-sm"><i class="fa-solid fa-sun accent-color"></i> Summer Mountain Adventure in Breckenridge</h3>
                    <p>In warmer months, Breckenridge offers scenic chairlift rides, hiking, mountain biking, climbing activities, alpine attractions, restaurants, shopping, and family-friendly outdoor recreation. It is an easy day trip for guests who want more activity while keeping the retreat itself quiet and private.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.breckenridge.com/explore-the-resort/activities-and-events/summer-activities.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline-accent btn-sm">Learn More <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100 p-4">
                    <h3 class="heading-sm"><i class="fa-solid fa-store accent-color"></i> Breckenridge Town, Dining, Shopping, and Events</h3>
                    <p>Breckenridge also offers historic mountain-town character, restaurants, coffee shops, shopping, galleries, events, and visitor services. This gives retreat guests access to town energy without staying in the middle of the tourist traffic.</p>
                    <a href="https://gobreck.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline-accent btn-sm">Learn More <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100 p-4">
                    <h3 class="heading-sm"><i class="fa-solid fa-mountain accent-color"></i> Mosquito Pass and High-Alpine Exploring</h3>
                    <p>The property sits near Mosquito Pass, one of Colorado's highest and most scenic mountain pass routes. The area is known for rugged alpine views, mining history, seasonal 4x4 access, photography, and high-country exploring between Alma and Leadville.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.leadvilletwinlakes.com/trail/mosquito-pass/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline-accent btn-sm">Learn More <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
                    <a href="https://exploreparkcounty.com/places/mosquito-pass-alma-co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline-accent btn-sm ms-2">Additional Info <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100 p-4">
                    <h3 class="heading-sm"><i class="fa-solid fa-fish accent-color"></i> Fishing Near Alma, Fairplay, and South Park</h3>
                    <p>The surrounding South Park region is known for trout fishing, with access to public fishing areas near Fairplay Beach, the South Platte River corridor, nearby reservoirs, mountain streams, and alpine lakes. Guests should follow Colorado Parks and Wildlife licensing rules.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.parkcountyco.gov/673/Fairplay-Beach-Recreation-Area" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline-accent btn-sm">Fairplay Beach <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
                    <a href="https://cpw.state.co.us/activities/fishing/fishing-licenses-and-dates" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline-accent btn-sm ms-2">Fishing License <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100 p-4">
                    <h3 class="heading-sm"><i class="fa-solid fa-person-hiking accent-color"></i> Hiking, Scenic Drives, and Wildlife Viewing</h3>
                    <p>Alma is a strong base for hiking, scenic drives, wildlife viewing, photography, and high-country day trips. Nearby draws include Mosquito Pass, Kite Lake, ghost town history, alpine trails, and wide-open mountain scenery. Moose, deer, foxes, and mountain birds are commonly seen in the area.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.colorado.com/cities-and-towns/alma" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline-accent btn-sm">Explore Alma <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
